				<p>The use of span, div, id, class. Span is inline tag which allows users to add anything to the content between span tag without making the content a block. Div is similar but making the contents to become a block, therefore easier to manage. ID is used to define one unique part of content that allowed to be styled in CSS. The same function for class, but class is much useful because it allows us to define as many contents as we want as a group. <a href="https://www.udacity.com/course/viewer#!/c-nd000/l-4131369051/m-4289099604" style="color:white">link</a> </p>
